OL,7,F"I would hope that people will be
OL,8,Fconcerned about how the government
OL,9,Fuses the power that it's given to it.
OL,11,F"I think if they were to take a second
OL,12,Fto think about what the government put
OL,13,Fthese people through, they might be a
OL,14,Fbit more sympathetic towards those
OL,15,Findividuals and any compensation that
OL,16,Fthey may or may not receive for them."
OL,18,FManston House, was designed to have a
OL,19,Fcapacity of 1600 people, but there
OL,20,Fbecame a bottleneck with more than
OL,21,F4,000.
OL,1,W~s1x0~s1~s hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}   G7/9
